-- Songbird Estates shareholder Madison backs Qatari bid
-- 
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 02:42AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 8 (Reuters) - The Qatar Investment Authority (QIA) said on Monday that Songbird Estates <SBDE.L> shareholder Madison International Realty said it plans to accept the sovereign wealth fund's hostile offer for the UK property firm.

The 350-pence-a-share offer for the owner of London's Canary Wharf financial district was launched to Songbird shareholders by the QIA and U.S. investor Brookfield Property Partners <BPY.N> on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0TO3S0] [ID:nL6N0TP0LA] Madison holds a total of 18,627,054 Songbird shares, representing approximately 12 percent of Songbird's shares in free float and 2.5 of Songbird's issued ordinary share capital.